Transforming Eastern Time to Local Time

Introduction

The date_time field in our Omniture implementation is in Eastern Time Zone. To do behavioral analysis with respect to time, we have to use local time. Since there is geo_zipcode field in the data, we can use that to get the time zone offset from GMT of each zip code. Once we get the offset, we can get the local time by first changing from Eastern Time to GMT and then by adding the offset.
